{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_41","type":"agent_message","text":"VERDICT: no. Bridge handoff and transplant ordering still have checkable wiring breaks before a build can be trusted.\n\nMUST-FIX BEFORE BUILD:\n1. [r3 input Carry-to-r3 / PATCH_PLAN #1] Bridge producer/consumer contract is split between “path” and “dict/JSON”. `OTR_BridgeArtifactEmit` returns only `artifact_path` as a `STRING` and writes to `bridge_out/` (`nodes.py:223-269`), while the staged production adapter validates an already-parsed `dict` and has no file/path loader (`transplant_work/production_new_modules/_otr_ledger_input_adapter.py:52-128`). Concrete fix: pick one contract. Either make the production writer socket accept a path and load+validate JSON through the adapter, or make the lab node output artifact JSON and have production parse that. Add one end-to-end test from emit output -> production validation.\n\n2. [r3 input Carry-to-r3 / PATCH_PLAN #1] Bridge artifact filenames can overwrite incompatible selections. The emitted path is `bridge_{source_bank_id}_{story_model_id}.json` (`nodes.py:265-267`), but the artifact identity also includes `story_pipeline_id` and `visual_style_id` (`src/upstream_story_lab/bridge.py:80-91`; `src/upstream_story_lab/contracts.py:424-446`). A user emitting the same bank/model with a different style or pipeline silently replaces the prior artifact. Concrete fix: include all resolved axes, or a stable artifact hash, in the filename and assert no accidental overwrite unless explicitly requested.\n\n3. [PATCH_PLAN #1/#2/#3/#5] The numbered transplant order calls new writer seams before their callees exist. `PATCH_PLAN #1` wires `compose_source_coda` from the writer (`transplant_work/PATCH_PLAN.md:24-45`), but `compose_source_coda` is only introduced in `PATCH_PLAN #2` and is absent from the mirrored `_otr_line_composer.py` public surface, which currently exposes `compose_news_coda` only (`production_mirror/nodes/_otr_line_composer.py:103-128`, `3386-3456`). Same issue for writer calls to new `pick_style` kwargs before `_otr_style_picker.pick_style` accepts them (`production_mirror/nodes/_otr_style_picker.py:783-792`) and `OutlineRequest` profile fields before `_otr_outline.OutlineRequest` has them (`production_mirror/nodes/_otr_outline.py:277-445`). Concrete fix: land callee API changes first, or make #1/#2/#3/#5 one atomic transplant chunk with import/signature smoke tests before workflow edits.\n\n4. [r3 input Carry-to-r3] `nodes.py` cache invalidation is not honest for mirror drift. The validator checks `production_mirror` drift (`nodes.py:111-127`), but `IS_CHANGED` hashes only `__init__.py`, `nodes.py`, `src/`, and `fixtures/` (`nodes.py:36-53`). If `production_mirror` changes, ComfyUI can reuse a stale validator result. Concrete fix: include `production_mirror/` and `PRODUCTION_MIRROR_MANIFEST.md` in the validator digest, or give the validator a separate digest that covers every drift input it reads.\n\n5. [PATCH_PLAN #1/#10] Appending writer inputs will break current production self-tests unless test/schema updates land in the same chunk. The mirrored writer hard-asserts `n_optional == 16` (`production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:5728-5739`), while `PATCH_PLAN #1` adds four widgets plus bridge/policy forceInput sockets (`transplant_work/PATCH_PLAN.md:40-49`). Concrete fix: update `INPUT_TYPES`, `run()` kwargs, self-test widget-count/order assertions, offline schemas, and workflow audits in one build step before touching the workflow JSON.\n\nSHOULD-FIX:\n1. [PATCH_PLAN #9] Whitelist wording is too narrow. The plan says “four new creative keys” (`transplant_work/PATCH_PLAN.md:81-82`), but `source_bank`, `story_model`, `story_pipeline`, and `visual_style` are routing/config keys, not ordinary creative knobs. Current whitelists do not include them (`production_mirror/scripts/otr_api.py:753-764`; `production_mirror/nodes/_otr_workflow_apply.py:489-517`). Concrete fix: name the exact added keys in both whitelists and add a parity test.\n\n2. [r3 input Folded #6] The “55 combos” claim is covered by pytest, not by the advertised headless validator path. `tests/test_matrix_and_leakage.py` checks pack x style combinations (`tests/test_matrix_and_leakage.py:39-65`), but `scripts/validate_lab.py` and the Comfy validator build one default-style spec per pack (`scripts/validate_lab.py:40-54`; `nodes.py:129-146`). Concrete fix: either make validate_lab validate the same 55 matrix or stop presenting validate_lab green as coverage for all styles.\n\n3. [PATCH_PLAN #1] verify: RSS external integration. The writer imports `story_orchestrator._fetch_science_news` for the only live third-party fetch path (`production_mirror/nodes/OTR_LedgerScriptWriter.py:1137-1158`), but `story_orchestrator.py` is not in `production_mirror/` per `PRODUCTION_MIRROR_MANIFEST.md`. Before transplant, verify import availability, retry/rate-limit behavior, and failure messages against live production.\n\nOPTIONAL / NICE-TO-HAVE:\n1. [nodes.py] Hide or clearly mark non-runnable `custom_source_bank` in lab emit choices. It is currently exposed by `_bank_choices()` (`nodes.py:56-57`) even though the registry marks it `runnable: false` (`fixtures/banks.json`) and `build_spec` will fail when no packet exists (`src/upstream_story_lab/registry.py:252-263`).\n\nCUT THESE (over-engineering):\n1. [r3 input Carry-to-r3] Cut any reliance on the `bridge_out/` folder convention as an integration mechanism. It is safe to cut because `PATCH_PLAN #1` already says the bridge input is explicit path/JSON and “the adapter never scans a conventional folder” (`transplant_work/PATCH_PLAN.md:42-45`). Explicit socket handoff is the smaller, testable contract."}}
